               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18590919-name-307" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18590919-name-307" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18590919-name-307" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18590919-name-307" type="given" value="THOMAS WILLIAM"></interp>THOMAS WILLIAM MASON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grocer, of Plaistow—on Saturday night, 20th August, the prisoner came for some bread and cheese—I sup<lb></lb>plied him and he went out—he came in again about two minutes afterwards, and I saw him go out again and take a piece of bacon from a board at the door—he passed the window with it in his hand—I could not get out quick enough to take him—I saw him in company with some one else at the Coach and Horses, about six yards from the shop door—I followed him in that direction—I am quite sure he is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What time was it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About half-past 10 o'clock—I do a middling trade—nobody else was in the shop but myself—the prisoner's employers came and bailed him.</p>
               <p>
